<TITLE> RMG factories fined for fire safety breaches </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gazipur, Apr 27(bdnews24.com)  A mobile court on Tuesday fined seven factories and a residential building for not following fire-safety requirements. The court collected around Tk 650,000 as fines from seven readymade garments factories and one multi-storey residential building. The operation took place between 10am and 3pm at Kashimpur and Konabari areas under the sadar upazila. Md Rafiqul Islam, deputy assistant director of district fire service, told bdnews24.com that they had fined Bismillah Knitting, Sagor Plastic Industries and Maa Knitting Fabrics Tk 100,000 each, Ashraf Knitting was fined Tk 75,000, and Zizam Sweater Factory was fined Tk 50,000 for not having fire licences and necessary fire fighting equipment. The court also fined two other factories  Niddle Web Knitwear Ltd and BSS Fashion and Design Warehouse  Tk 100,000 for having failed to renew their licences. The official also said that the owner of OA Tower at Hakkani Society area in the town, Aiyubur Rahman, was fined Tk 20,000 for fire safety violations. bdnews24.com/c
